items.title: Awesome Jupyter
items.content_text:
### JupyterLab Extensions

*   [code\_formatter (⭐884)](https://github.com/ryantam626/jupyterlab_code_formatter) - A universal code formatter.
*   [nb\_black (⭐367)](https://github.com/dnanhkhoa/nb_black) - Extension to keep Python code automatically formatted using [black (⭐40k)](https://github.com/psf/black).
*   [python-bytecode (⭐62)](https://github.com/jtpio/jupyterlab-python-bytecode) - Explore CPython Bytecode in JupyterLab.
*   [quickopen (⭐85)](https://github.com/parente/jupyterlab-quickopen) - Quickly open a file in JupyterLab by typing part of its name.
*   [sidecar (⭐257)](https://github.com/jupyter-widgets/jupyterlab-sidecar) - A sidecar output widget for JupyterLab.
*   [sql (⭐428)](https://github.com/pbugnion/jupyterlab-sql) - SQL GUI for JupyterLab.
*   [system-monitor (⭐302)](https://github.com/jtpio/jupyterlab-system-monitor) - Extension to display system metrics.
*   [theme-darcula (⭐217)](https://github.com/telamonian/theme-darcula) - A handsome Darcula theme for Jupyterlab.
*   [topbar (⭐6)](https://github.com/jtpio/jupyterlab-topbar) - Top Bar extension for JupyterLab.
*   [vim (⭐982)](https://github.com/jwkvam/jupyterlab-vim) - Vim notebook cell bindings.
items.content_html:
JupyterLab Extensions

  • code_formatter (⭐884) - A universal code formatter.
  • nb_black (⭐367) - Extension to keep Python code automatically formatted using black (⭐40k).
  • python-bytecode (⭐62) - Explore CPython Bytecode in JupyterLab.
  • quickopen (⭐85) - Quickly open a file in JupyterLab by typing part of its name.
  • sidecar (⭐257) - A sidecar output widget for JupyterLab.
  • sql (⭐428) - SQL GUI for JupyterLab.
  • system-monitor (⭐302) - Extension to display system metrics.
  • theme-darcula (⭐217) - A handsome Darcula theme for Jupyterlab.
  • topbar (⭐6) - Top Bar extension for JupyterLab.
  • vim (⭐982) - Vim notebook cell bindings.

items.title: Awesome Ctf
items.content_text:
### Bruteforcers

*   [Hydra](https://tools.kali.org/password-attacks/hydra) - A parallelized login cracker which supports numerous protocols to attack

### Steganography

*   [Image Steganography](https://sourceforge.net/projects/image-steg/) - Embeds text and files in images with optional encryption. Easy-to-use UI.
*   [Image Steganography Online](https://incoherency.co.uk/image-steganography) - This is a client-side Javascript tool to steganographically hide images inside the lower "bits" of other images

### Writeups Collections

*   [0e85dc6eaf (⭐97)](https://github.com/0e85dc6eaf/CTF-Writeups) - Write-ups for CTF challenges by 0e85dc6eaf
*   [Mzfr (⭐122)](https://github.com/mzfr/ctf-writeups/) - CTF competition write-ups by mzfr
*   [SababaSec (⭐20)](https://github.com/SababaSec/ctf-writeups) - A collection of CTF write-ups by the SababaSec team
items.content_html:
Bruteforcers

  • Hydra - A parallelized login cracker which supports numerous protocols to attack

Steganography

  • Image Steganography - Embeds text and files in images with optional encryption. Easy-to-use UI.
  • Image Steganography Online - This is a client-side Javascript tool to steganographically hide images inside the lower "bits" of other images

items.title: Awesome Dataviz
items.content_text:
### React Native / Misc

*   [Vega-Lite](https://vega.github.io/vega-lite/) - is a high-level grammar of interactive graphics. It provides a concise JSON syntax for rapidly generating visualizations to support analysis.

items.title: Awesome Streaming
items.content_text:
### Table of Contents / DSL

*   [Apache Beam (⭐8.2k)](https://github.com/apache/beam) \[Java, Python, SQL, Scala, Go] - unified model and set of language-specific SDKs for defining and executing data processing workflows, and also data ingestion and integration flows, supporting Enterprise Integration Patterns (EIPs) and Domain Specific Languages (DSLs), open sourced by Google.

### Table of Contents / Closed Source

*   [Cloud Dataflow](https://cloud.google.com/dataflow/)\[Java, Python, SQL, Scala] - Google's managed stream and batch data processing engine. Supports running Beam pipelines.
